WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.134 --> 00:00:02.504
[Amanda]
<i>Previously on</i> Will Trent...

2
00:00:02.637 --> 00:00:03.771
This is Antonio.

3
00:00:03.905 --> 00:00:06.006
<i>-He's my uncle.</i>
<i>-Lucy's brother.</i>

4
00:00:06.139 --> 00:00:07.575
Family is everything.

5
00:00:07.709 --> 00:00:09.811
[Amanda] <i>Lucy Morales.</i>
<i>she was your mother.</i>

6
00:00:09.944 --> 00:00:11.445
<i>She died in childbirth.</i>

7
00:00:11.579 --> 00:00:13.380
-Where did you get that?
-Bitch. it's mine. Hands off.

8
00:00:13.515 --> 00:00:15.215
Hand it over. It's Lucy's.

9
00:00:15.717 --> 00:00:17.451
I loved your mother.
Maybe I can love you.

10
00:00:17.585 --> 00:00:19.921
You killed her.
then put me in a trash can.

11
00:00:20.053 --> 00:00:22.624
<i>You murdered sex workers</i>
<i>and sewed their mouths shut.</i>

12
00:00:22.757 --> 00:00:24.926
[James] <i>You know the way</i>
<i>the mind of a serialist works.</i>

13
00:00:25.058 --> 00:00:26.528
<i>Show me one painted fingernail.</i>

14
00:00:27.227 --> 00:00:28.730
[gunshot]

15
00:00:28.863 --> 00:00:30.632
[Caleb] <i>I hope it brings you</i>
<i>relief that he's gone.</i>

16
00:00:30.765 --> 00:00:32.199
[James] <i>You like it.</i>

17
00:00:32.332 --> 00:00:33.735
How's it going with Daddy?

18
00:00:33.868 --> 00:00:35.003
Where'd you get this? No.

19
00:00:35.135 --> 00:00:36.069
[distorted voices]

20
00:00:36.203 --> 00:00:38.171
Get out of my head!

21
00:00:38.305 --> 00:00:39.774
[electronic screeching]

22
00:00:43.711 --> 00:00:45.078
I don't know.

23
00:00:45.914 --> 00:00:47.281
Are we sure I'm not crazy?

24
00:00:47.414 --> 00:00:50.050
[Dr. Roach] We don't really use
that word anymore.

25
00:00:50.183 --> 00:00:51.853
Is this about Ulster?

26
00:00:52.219 --> 00:00:54.022
Are you still hearing him
in your head?

27
00:00:54.154 --> 00:00:55.890
He's driving me nuts.

28
00:00:56.024 --> 00:00:57.792
[Betty whines]

29
00:00:57.926 --> 00:00:59.226
[sighs]

30
00:00:59.359 --> 00:01:01.295
See? That's the look
I was trying to avoid.

31
00:01:01.428 --> 00:01:04.599
[scoffs] Stop projecting.
This is my listening face.

32
00:01:04.732 --> 00:01:05.867
Are you using the tools?

33
00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.368
Exercise. podcast. work.

34
00:01:08.503 --> 00:01:10.538
I do miss sitting still
and relaxing. though.

35
00:01:10.972 --> 00:01:14.842
I think that you live
a rich and creative inner life.

36
00:01:14.976 --> 00:01:19.479
and you do it to make
sense of a world that
just doesn't make any sense.

37
00:01:20.347 --> 00:01:21.649
Or I'm crazy.

38
00:01:22.416 --> 00:01:27.220
So. when Ulster shows up.
does it seem like
he's actually there?

39
00:01:28.056 --> 00:01:29.389
No.

40
00:01:29.524 --> 00:01:31.425
-Well. I can tell
the difference.
-See?

41
00:01:32.794 --> 00:01:34.294
Not crazy.

42
00:01:34.428 --> 00:01:36.030
We all hear voices in our head.

43
00:01:36.163 --> 00:01:39.968
Sometimes they're annoying
or downright destructive.

44
00:01:40.535 --> 00:01:44.038
but usually they're
just trying to help us
in their own misguided way.

45
00:01:44.171 --> 00:01:46.574
-Whose side are you on?
-[Dr. Roach] It's not Ulster.

46
00:01:46.708 --> 00:01:47.842
He's you.

47
00:01:48.308 --> 00:01:51.244
He's a part of you
that needs to be heard.

48
00:01:51.378 --> 00:01:53.380
So. let's start with this.

49
00:01:53.514 --> 00:01:56.884
The next time he shows up.
rebrand him.

50
00:01:57.919 --> 00:01:59.053
Rebrand him?

51
00:01:59.186 --> 00:02:01.656
Give him a new name.
a new look.

52
00:02:01.789 --> 00:02:03.057
Take his fangs away.

53
00:02:03.190 --> 00:02:06.293
It's your brain.
You call the shots.

54
00:02:07.061 --> 00:02:08.796
He can't hurt you anymore.

55
00:02:09.396 --> 00:02:10.698
Unless you let him.

56
00:02:12.934 --> 00:02:14.167
[sighs]

57
00:02:18.940 --> 00:02:20.541
What do we got?

58
00:02:20.675 --> 00:02:23.778
[exhales] Male. 24. found tied
to his own bed about 3:00 a.m.

59
00:02:23.911 --> 00:02:25.412
Multiple stab wounds
to the chest.

60
00:02:25.546 --> 00:02:28.583
Okay. so why call me?

61
00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:36.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

62
00:02:45.566 --> 00:02:47.702
[chuckles] Is this a sick joke?

63
00:02:47.835 --> 00:02:49.904
[exhales]
It's got to be a copycat.

64
00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:52.607
Someone who knew about Ulster.

65
00:02:55.810 --> 00:02:57.011
When did he die?

66
00:02:57.145 --> 00:02:58.680
Uh. early a.m.

67
00:02:58.813 --> 00:03:01.082
Some defensive wounds.
but not many.

68
00:03:01.214 --> 00:03:02.517
Probably asleep
when it started.

69
00:03:02.650 --> 00:03:04.619
-Amanda know about this?
-[Angie] I texted her.

70
00:03:04.752 --> 00:03:07.387
She's at her support group.
She'll be here any minute.

71
00:03:11.159 --> 00:03:12.960
Red nail polish is off.

72
00:03:14.028 --> 00:03:15.863
This is more vermilion.

73
00:03:17.364 --> 00:03:19.867
The stitches are sloppy.
They rushed it.

74
00:03:20.001 --> 00:03:22.570
Probably an amateur
chasing headlines. [inhales]

75
00:03:23.236 --> 00:03:25.773
Appreciate the heads-up.
I'll help out however I can.

76
00:03:25.907 --> 00:03:27.842
I'll let you take
the lead on it.

77
00:03:27.975 --> 00:03:29.777
[door opens]

78
00:03:29.911 --> 00:03:32.814
Got an ID on our John Doe.
Trent. you're gonna
want to hear this.

79
00:03:34.115 --> 00:03:35.917
His name's Antonio Morales.

80
00:03:36.050 --> 00:03:37.484
[♪ ominous music plays]

81
00:03:41.089 --> 00:03:42.322
Eduardo. call Antonio.

82
00:03:42.456 --> 00:03:44.192
<i>Calling Antonio</i> .

83
00:03:44.324 --> 00:03:45.960
-[line ringing]
-[Antonio] ¡Saludos!

84
00:03:46.094 --> 00:03:48.129
<i>-You've reached</i>
<i>Antonio Morales</i> .
-[Will exhales]

85
00:03:48.261 --> 00:03:49.496
Damn it.

86
00:03:49.630 --> 00:03:51.733
Is there any way
the name is a coincidence?

87
00:03:51.866 --> 00:03:54.502
Copycat Ulster kills a guy
with my uncle's name.

88
00:03:54.635 --> 00:03:55.803
drops him in our laps.

89
00:03:55.937 --> 00:03:57.237
That's some coincidence.

90
00:03:57.370 --> 00:03:59.040
-[line ringing]
-¡Saludos!

91
00:03:59.173 --> 00:04:00.942
But why? What's the play?

92
00:04:01.075 --> 00:04:03.711
Feels like we're dealing with
a lunatic who knows about me

93
00:04:03.845 --> 00:04:05.913
and he's coming after
my family.

94
00:04:06.047 --> 00:04:09.550
or there's a serial killer
specializing in men
named Antonio Morales.

95
00:04:09.684 --> 00:04:11.318
Either way. I gotta go.

96
00:04:13.487 --> 00:04:14.655
Go where?

97
00:04:14.789 --> 00:04:16.389
[airplane passing overhead]

98
00:04:16.524 --> 00:04:18.626
[singer]
♪ <i>Puerto Rico Puerto Rico</i> ♪

99
00:04:18.760 --> 00:04:20.928
[Amanda on phone] <i>Puerto Rico?</i>
<i>You could have given me</i>
<i>some advance notice.</i>

100
00:04:21.062 --> 00:04:23.064
It's a three-hour flight.
I'll be home before dark.

101
00:04:23.197 --> 00:04:24.999
<i>I wanted to get here</i>
<i>as soon as I could.</i>

102
00:04:25.133 --> 00:04:27.769
-Well. that could have been a--
-Coincidence? Yeah. I know.

103
00:04:27.902 --> 00:04:28.936
You believe that?

104
00:04:29.637 --> 00:04:31.239
-No.
-[Will] <i>Me neither.</i>

105
00:04:31.371 --> 00:04:32.774
Antonio's my family.

106
00:04:32.907 --> 00:04:34.407
I only have two blood relatives
left on the planet.

107
00:04:34.542 --> 00:04:36.544
and I need to know he's okay.

108
00:04:36.677 --> 00:04:38.579
[Amanda] There are cops
on that island who could've
taken care of that for you.

109
00:04:38.713 --> 00:04:40.114
or you could've brought Faith.

110
00:04:40.748 --> 00:04:42.517
Look. I don't want to argue
about the past.

111
00:04:42.650 --> 00:04:44.085
[Faith] <i>Okay.</i>
<i>let's talk about the leads.</i>

112
00:04:44.218 --> 00:04:45.787
Boot print at the scene.

113
00:04:45.920 --> 00:04:48.288
Tread matches a vintage boot
with a narrow pool of buyers.

114
00:04:48.421 --> 00:04:51.726
One of them also bought
a Ka-Bar with a blade that
matches the Morales wounds.

115
00:04:51.859 --> 00:04:53.928
He sounds interesting.
Who's this guy?

116
00:04:54.061 --> 00:04:56.396
Jebediah Oswald. ex-con.

117
00:04:56.531 --> 00:04:58.365
Petty assault.
indecent exposure.

118
00:04:58.498 --> 00:05:02.136
He's no mastermind.
but he's got a screw loose
and a nasty streak.

119
00:05:02.270 --> 00:05:04.672
-I like him for this.
-We're tracking the address.

120
00:05:04.806 --> 00:05:07.575
All right. This is it.
I got to go. Keep me posted.

121
00:05:10.278 --> 00:05:11.311
[buzzing]

122
00:05:11.779 --> 00:05:13.413
[person] Agent Trent?

123
00:05:14.248 --> 00:05:15.783
Agent Elkie. FBI.

124
00:05:17.118 --> 00:05:19.554
-Who sent you?
-You were flagged
at the airport.

125
00:05:19.687 --> 00:05:21.556
Why is GBI poking around
on federal turf?

126
00:05:21.689 --> 00:05:24.192
Not poking around.
Checking in on my uncle.

127
00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:25.827
-You tried...
-Antonio!

128
00:05:26.493 --> 00:05:29.396
-You tried calling him?
-Oh. No. uh.
hadn't thought of that.

129
00:05:29.530 --> 00:05:31.732
Yes. I called him
dozens of times.

130
00:05:31.866 --> 00:05:32.867
[buzzing]

131
00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:34.401
You sure he's not busy?

132
00:05:34.535 --> 00:05:36.871
He's single.
he's on sabbatical.
and he always picks up.

133
00:05:37.839 --> 00:05:40.007
Agent Trent. you break
that door. you break the law.

134
00:05:40.141 --> 00:05:41.441
I'm GBI. Antonio!

135
00:05:41.576 --> 00:05:43.110
GBI has no jurisdiction
in Puerto Rico.

136
00:05:43.244 --> 00:05:45.580
He's my family. okay?
And I need to find him.

137
00:05:45.713 --> 00:05:47.548
I need to know he's okay.

138
00:05:51.185 --> 00:05:52.352
[buzzing]

139
00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:53.988
[person speaks Spanish
on intercom]

140
00:05:54.121 --> 00:05:56.389
[speaks Spanish]

141
00:05:59.459 --> 00:06:00.995
Antonio Morales.

142
00:06:01.596 --> 00:06:02.797
[speaks Spanish]

143
00:06:06.133 --> 00:06:07.602
[door buzzing]

144
00:06:10.638 --> 00:06:11.873
You coming?

145
00:06:24.484 --> 00:06:25.887
[person groaning]

146
00:06:26.020 --> 00:06:27.822
[♪ suspenseful music plays]

147
00:06:31.325 --> 00:06:32.627
[groaning continues]

148
00:06:45.573 --> 00:06:46.674
FBI!

149
00:06:46.807 --> 00:06:48.075
[shouting in Spanish]

150
00:06:48.209 --> 00:06:49.476
[speaks Spanish]

151
00:06:49.610 --> 00:06:51.746
-What the hell?
-Antonio. Antonio. it's me.

152
00:06:51.879 --> 00:06:54.081
Will? Will. what the hell
are you doing here?

153
00:06:54.215 --> 00:06:56.483
[both speaking Spanish]

154
00:07:04.625 --> 00:07:06.527
<i>-Por favor. Sofia.</i>
<i>-¡Déjame!</i>

155
00:07:06.661 --> 00:07:08.162
[door slams]

156
00:07:11.966 --> 00:07:13.668
[in English]
Don't you call first?

157
00:07:13.801 --> 00:07:15.435
You know. I called ten times.
I thought you were dead.

158
00:07:15.569 --> 00:07:16.904
I was busy.

159
00:07:17.038 --> 00:07:18.105
Well. obviously.

160
00:07:18.239 --> 00:07:19.240
And you are?

161
00:07:19.373 --> 00:07:21.342
Lana Elkie. FBI.

162
00:07:21.474 --> 00:07:22.643
Antonio Morales.

163
00:07:22.777 --> 00:07:25.513
As you can see.
I am very much alive.

164
00:07:25.646 --> 00:07:27.715
and in demand.

165
00:07:27.848 --> 00:07:33.453
Tell me. how did a lovely
creature like you end up in
an organization like that?

166
00:07:33.587 --> 00:07:35.656
And with such soft hands too.

167
00:07:35.790 --> 00:07:37.692
Okay. you can
let go of her hands now.

168
00:07:37.825 --> 00:07:41.629
Look. I'm sorry that
I ruined your sexy time.
but... [inhales. exhales]

169
00:07:41.762 --> 00:07:43.197
...I. for one.
am happy you're alive.

170
00:07:43.331 --> 00:07:45.266
Ah. forget it. She was married.

171
00:07:45.399 --> 00:07:47.001
You probably did me a favor.

172
00:07:47.134 --> 00:07:48.569
Look. Antonio.

173
00:07:48.970 --> 00:07:50.805
I need you
to listen to me. okay?

174
00:07:51.238 --> 00:07:52.472
Your life is in danger.

175
00:07:52.606 --> 00:07:57.044
Will. you're here.
You're here. [chuckles]

176
00:07:57.611 --> 00:07:59.213
That's tremendous.

177
00:08:00.014 --> 00:08:04.051
Oh. man. you look thirsty.
and so do you.

178
00:08:04.185 --> 00:08:05.119
Who's drinking?

179
00:08:05.252 --> 00:08:06.253
Um...

180
00:08:06.387 --> 00:08:08.055
Let me put on some pants.

181
00:08:09.223 --> 00:08:10.291
Make yourselves at home.

182
00:08:10.858 --> 00:08:12.560
-That's my uncle.
-Mmm.

183
00:08:12.994 --> 00:08:14.028
Yeah.

184
00:08:33.347 --> 00:08:35.049
Oh. jewel of the junkyard.

185
00:08:37.585 --> 00:08:40.287
Jebediah Oswald. GBI. open up.

186
00:08:48.863 --> 00:08:50.598
[♪ eerie music plays]

187
00:09:04.645 --> 00:09:06.113
[grunts]

188
00:09:07.715 --> 00:09:08.949
[exhales]

189
00:09:10.818 --> 00:09:12.086
[rattling]

190
00:09:22.229 --> 00:09:23.998
[knocking on window]

191
00:09:25.499 --> 00:09:27.635
Geez. Really?

192
00:09:30.771 --> 00:09:32.006
[person screams]

193
00:09:32.139 --> 00:09:34.575
[Michael] GBI! Stop!
Hey. he's running!

194
00:09:35.976 --> 00:09:37.578
[Faith] Oswald. stop!

195
00:09:38.379 --> 00:09:39.713
[Michael] Hey. stop!

196
00:09:48.189 --> 00:09:49.356
Oh.

197
00:09:51.759 --> 00:09:53.327
[Michael] GBI. stop!

198
00:09:55.564 --> 00:09:56.831
Hey!

199
00:10:07.074 --> 00:10:08.976
[Angie whispers] What the f...

200
00:10:16.518 --> 00:10:17.852
[Michael grunts]

201
00:10:18.819 --> 00:10:20.020
[groans]

202
00:10:23.657 --> 00:10:25.893
[Oswald panting] No.

203
00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:27.695
[screaming]

204
00:10:30.264 --> 00:10:31.866
[rattling]

205
00:10:49.518 --> 00:10:50.918
[Antonio laughing]

206
00:10:53.454 --> 00:10:55.756
[Antonio] I know
what you're thinking--

207
00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:58.025
piña colada. touristy--

208
00:10:58.159 --> 00:11:01.028
but we must reclaim
what is ours.

209
00:11:02.062 --> 00:11:05.666
You know this drink originated
right here in San Juan
in the '50s?

210
00:11:06.100 --> 00:11:09.803
<i>Chacho.</i> quit being
a bloodhound for a minute
and cut the garnish.

211
00:11:09.937 --> 00:11:13.007
You know. the lock on your door
is busted. Someone could
just walk right in.

212
00:11:13.140 --> 00:11:16.043
-It's been like that forever.
-I can post
a couple of guys outside.

213
00:11:16.177 --> 00:11:18.412
No. no. no. One fed
in my kitchen is bad enough.

214
00:11:18.547 --> 00:11:21.148
You put cops out there.
my friends will never
talk to me again.

215
00:11:21.282 --> 00:11:23.552
Look. I need you
to take this seriously. okay?

216
00:11:23.684 --> 00:11:26.954
A man named Antonio Morales
was found tied in his house.

217
00:11:27.087 --> 00:11:28.789
-his mouth was sewn--
-Yeah. in Atlanta. In Atlanta.

218
00:11:28.923 --> 00:11:31.959
You think this psycho's
booking a ticket down here
just to off me?

219
00:11:32.092 --> 00:11:33.761
-You know. I-I have my bat...
-[Will exhales]

220
00:11:33.894 --> 00:11:36.730
...and a hell of a swing
if the bastard
wants to come for me.

221
00:11:36.864 --> 00:11:40.034
Now. the best part
of this drink is...

222
00:11:41.603 --> 00:11:44.238
it comes with a fun umbrella.
which I collect.

223
00:11:46.575 --> 00:11:51.111
Her name was Maria.
on a beach in Arecibo.
drinking a mai tai.

224
00:11:51.245 --> 00:11:53.781
Her eyes were
the color of the ocean.

225
00:11:57.885 --> 00:11:59.353
<i>Salud.</i>

226
00:12:05.059 --> 00:12:06.260
[Antonio] Mmm.

227
00:12:07.562 --> 00:12:10.931
Will. I can't believe it took
this mess to get you down here.

228
00:12:11.432 --> 00:12:12.667
You remember our pact?

229
00:12:13.167 --> 00:12:14.735
Visit each other once a year.

230
00:12:14.868 --> 00:12:16.538
That was almost two years ago.

231
00:12:17.037 --> 00:12:18.739
Well. we FaceTime.

232
00:12:18.872 --> 00:12:20.508
Not the same thing. Two years.

233
00:12:20.642 --> 00:12:22.409
I'm sorry. All right? Um...

234
00:12:23.043 --> 00:12:26.046
-I've had a lot going on.
-What's more important
than family?

235
00:12:26.180 --> 00:12:29.350
Hey. will you take
that jacket off? I feel like
I'm about to get audited.

236
00:12:29.483 --> 00:12:32.186
-[Elkie. Antonio chuckle]
-[automated voice]
Sofia llamando.

237
00:12:32.319 --> 00:12:33.588
Oh. [chuckles]

238
00:12:33.722 --> 00:12:36.056
Excuse me. I gotta take this.

239
00:12:36.625 --> 00:12:39.927
[speaking Spanish]

240
00:12:40.761 --> 00:12:46.200
[chuckles] Wow. he's quite
the romantic. Need help?

241
00:12:46.701 --> 00:12:49.036
-I got it.
-I beg to differ.

242
00:12:50.639 --> 00:12:52.540
Really? Okay.

243
00:13:02.216 --> 00:13:04.485
Wow. Where'd you learn
to do that?

244
00:13:04.619 --> 00:13:06.887
They teach you
all kinds of things in the FBI.

245
00:13:07.021 --> 00:13:09.056
[Will] Mmm. Hmm.

246
00:13:11.792 --> 00:13:13.260
Good. right?

247
00:13:15.630 --> 00:13:16.930
You guys gotta go.

248
00:13:17.064 --> 00:13:18.767
What? W-Why? What happened?

249
00:13:18.899 --> 00:13:20.434
Sofia's coming back over.

250
00:13:20.568 --> 00:13:24.471
I mean. it took some talking.
but she's. uh. ready to...

251
00:13:24.838 --> 00:13:25.774
rekindle.

252
00:13:25.906 --> 00:13:27.107
[Will exhales]

253
00:13:27.241 --> 00:13:29.243
[Antonio] Okay.
<i>Pa' fuera. Vámonos.</i>

254
00:13:29.678 --> 00:13:32.146
Let's go. Let's get a move on.
Oh. you know what?

255
00:13:32.279 --> 00:13:35.015
Rio's serves the best cocktails
on the island.

256
00:13:35.149 --> 00:13:36.751
You tell them Antonio sent you.

257
00:13:36.884 --> 00:13:38.986
What happened to family being
the most important thing. huh?

258
00:13:39.119 --> 00:13:41.188
Will. I need to
teach you something.

259
00:13:41.322 --> 00:13:44.024
When you're my age and you have
a chance to get laid.

260
00:13:44.158 --> 00:13:46.126
-you take it. Okay?
-[phone chimes]

261
00:13:46.260 --> 00:13:48.262
-Let's go. Come on. Let's go.
<i>-</i> [Eduardo] <i>Text from</i>
<i>Amanda Wagner.</i>

262
00:13:48.395 --> 00:13:50.964
<i>Suspect in custody. Jeb Oswald.</i>

263
00:13:51.098 --> 00:13:54.268
<i>Prints match the Morales scene.</i>
<i>Looks solid.</i>

264
00:13:54.401 --> 00:13:56.236
See? Everything worked out.

265
00:13:56.370 --> 00:13:58.740
I'll see you at Rio's
in a couple of hours.
Okay. Bye.

266
00:13:58.872 --> 00:14:01.909
[Eduardo] <i>Hope you're enjoying</i>
<i>your vacation. Eye roll emoji.</i>

267
00:14:04.845 --> 00:14:06.246
[Jeb sighs]

268
00:14:06.380 --> 00:14:09.149
[Angie] What is your connection
to Antonio Morales?

269
00:14:11.485 --> 00:14:12.520
Who?

270
00:14:15.422 --> 00:14:16.624
Oh. him.

271
00:14:17.024 --> 00:14:18.359
Why'd you kill him?

272
00:14:18.727 --> 00:14:20.160
Just following orders.

273
00:14:20.294 --> 00:14:21.629
[Faith] Whose orders?

274
00:14:23.798 --> 00:14:26.100
Who gave you the orders. Jeb?

275
00:14:26.233 --> 00:14:28.869
Does this have something
to do with James Ulster?

276
00:14:29.604 --> 00:14:30.971
Maybe. [chuckles]

277
00:14:31.105 --> 00:14:32.339
Maybe not.

278
00:14:32.707 --> 00:14:35.008
Okay. Listen up. asshole.

279
00:14:35.142 --> 00:14:37.645
You're facing
first-degree murder.
aggravating factors.

280
00:14:37.779 --> 00:14:41.482
Start talking or you're
looking at a dark room
all alone till you're dead.

281
00:14:41.616 --> 00:14:43.050
Facts.

282
00:14:43.818 --> 00:14:45.319
I wrote him a letter.

283
00:14:46.621 --> 00:14:48.322
I sent it to the jail.

284
00:14:49.022 --> 00:14:50.224
Fan mail.

285
00:14:50.859 --> 00:14:52.359
Told him I liked his work.

286
00:14:53.994 --> 00:14:55.462
Go on.

287
00:14:56.196 --> 00:14:58.165
He ain't wrote back.

288
00:14:58.298 --> 00:15:00.668
I figured. hell. big shot
like him. he probably gets
a whole pile of them.

289
00:15:00.802 --> 00:15:02.102
[chuckles]

290
00:15:03.437 --> 00:15:05.406
But then two weeks ago.
he did write back.

291
00:15:05.540 --> 00:15:08.275
James Ulster's been dead
for nearly two months.

292
00:15:10.745 --> 00:15:12.346
That's what you think.

293
00:15:16.684 --> 00:15:18.285
What did the letter say?

294
00:15:20.087 --> 00:15:21.321
Jeb.

295
00:15:22.189 --> 00:15:24.425
Just instructions. [sniffs]

296
00:15:24.559 --> 00:15:26.193
Name. address.

297
00:15:27.027 --> 00:15:28.328
what to do to him.

298
00:15:29.296 --> 00:15:31.498
-You still have it?
-I burned it.

299
00:15:31.900 --> 00:15:33.434
Convenient.

300
00:15:34.234 --> 00:15:35.570
I got a letter.

301
00:15:36.236 --> 00:15:38.071
That's how he talked to me.

302
00:15:40.441 --> 00:15:44.244
-That's how
he talked to all of us.
-[Angie] "Us"?

303
00:15:45.012 --> 00:15:47.448
Who is "us." Jeb?

304
00:15:47.981 --> 00:15:49.684
[♪ eerie music plays]

305
00:15:52.887 --> 00:15:54.589
[♪ singing in Spanish]

306
00:16:11.004 --> 00:16:14.007
[Elkie laughs]

307
00:16:16.210 --> 00:16:17.712
[chuckles]

308
00:16:19.146 --> 00:16:21.081
[chuckling continues]

309
00:16:24.485 --> 00:16:25.687
Um... no.

310
00:16:26.186 --> 00:16:27.488
[speaks Spanish]

311
00:16:28.690 --> 00:16:29.724
No. thank you.

312
00:16:34.896 --> 00:16:36.296
Come on. Trent.

313
00:16:38.867 --> 00:16:40.100
Live a little.

314
00:16:44.806 --> 00:16:46.039
[singing stops]

315
00:16:47.107 --> 00:16:48.141
[speaks Spanish]

316
00:16:48.275 --> 00:16:49.644
[crowd applauding. cheering]

317
00:16:50.344 --> 00:16:51.646
[♪ Latin jazz playing]

318
00:17:01.021 --> 00:17:02.422
[Elkie chuckles]

319
00:17:04.291 --> 00:17:06.528
[speaking Spanish]

320
00:17:22.342 --> 00:17:23.711
[glass shatters]

321
00:17:24.913 --> 00:17:26.915
[speaking Spanish]

322
00:17:27.047 --> 00:17:28.816
[Will] Um... [speaking Spanish]

323
00:17:30.552 --> 00:17:32.419
[in English]
Uh. I'm sorry. Uh...

324
00:17:33.821 --> 00:17:35.055
Uh...

325
00:17:38.593 --> 00:17:41.863
Everyone here is just
so friendly. [chuckles]

326
00:17:42.897 --> 00:17:45.733
Well. I'm sure people
are friendly wherever you go.

327
00:17:48.603 --> 00:17:49.704
Hold still.

328
00:17:50.103 --> 00:17:52.540
-[Will] Oh.
-It's just a baby.

329
00:17:53.240 --> 00:17:55.108
You're not scared of spiders.
are you?

330
00:17:56.076 --> 00:17:57.679
No. no. No.

331
00:17:57.812 --> 00:17:59.112
[chuckles]

332
00:17:59.581 --> 00:18:00.515
No.

333
00:18:00.648 --> 00:18:01.516
[chuckles]

334
00:18:01.916 --> 00:18:04.117
-[phone chimes]
-[Eduardo] <i>Call from Amanda.</i>

335
00:18:04.586 --> 00:18:06.821
<i>-Call from Amanda.</i>
-Oh. Excuse me.

336
00:18:08.088 --> 00:18:09.389
What do you got?

337
00:18:09.524 --> 00:18:11.593
Oswald just gave us
something concerning.

338
00:18:11.960 --> 00:18:13.528
He might not be acting alone.

339
00:18:14.028 --> 00:18:15.530
What'd he say?

340
00:18:15.663 --> 00:18:18.432
That someone calling themselves
Ulster sent him a letter.

341
00:18:18.566 --> 00:18:20.635
and he's not the only one
who got one.

342
00:18:21.069 --> 00:18:22.436
[Will] <i>Do you believe him?</i>

343
00:18:23.403 --> 00:18:24.606
[Amanda] <i>I don't know.</i>

344
00:18:25.105 --> 00:18:26.340
I have to go.

345
00:18:29.577 --> 00:18:30.344
Antonio!

346
00:18:30.477 --> 00:18:31.746
I'll check the back.

347
00:18:33.413 --> 00:18:34.816
[Will] Antonio!

348
00:18:38.118 --> 00:18:39.453
Antonio!

349
00:18:40.588 --> 00:18:42.322
[♪ eerie music plays]

350
00:18:57.839 --> 00:19:00.108
Bedroom's clear.
I called for backup.

351
00:19:00.240 --> 00:19:01.643
Any sign of your uncle?

352
00:19:04.979 --> 00:19:06.346
He's gone.

353
00:19:08.415 --> 00:19:10.652
[chattering in Spanish]

354
00:19:11.385 --> 00:19:14.187
[speaking Spanish]

355
00:19:15.389 --> 00:19:17.190
[in English]
Have-Have you ever seen him?

356
00:19:17.659 --> 00:19:19.627
Um...
[stutters. speaks Spanish]

357
00:19:19.761 --> 00:19:21.829
[in English] This man...
[speaks Spanish]

358
00:19:21.963 --> 00:19:23.163
[passerby] <i>No.</i>

359
00:19:23.798 --> 00:19:28.069
Will. Your Spanish.
[singsongy] Someone's
been practicing.

360
00:19:28.201 --> 00:19:29.771
[grunts]

361
00:19:29.904 --> 00:19:32.974
What did you do?
What did you do. huh?

362
00:19:33.107 --> 00:19:34.642
Hey. hey. Easy.

363
00:19:36.978 --> 00:19:38.211
That's right.

364
00:19:38.946 --> 00:19:40.447
You work for me now.

365
00:19:40.581 --> 00:19:42.583
You're not Ulster. you're a...

366
00:19:43.951 --> 00:19:46.319
-You're an elf.
-What do you mean. an elf?

367
00:19:46.453 --> 00:19:48.455
You mean like a cool elf
with a bow and an arrow?

368
00:19:48.589 --> 00:19:50.625
No. you make cookies.
You live in a tree. [chuckles]

369
00:19:50.758 --> 00:19:52.492
I think you've finally lost
that marble.

370
00:19:52.627 --> 00:19:56.097
No. You're gonna help me
find my uncle.

371
00:19:56.229 --> 00:19:57.632
[Elkie] Agent Trent?

372
00:19:59.033 --> 00:20:00.500
Sorry to send you away.

373
00:20:00.635 --> 00:20:02.503
The local guys get testy
if it's an agent
they don't know.

374
00:20:02.637 --> 00:20:04.672
I-It's not my jurisdiction.
Understood.

375
00:20:04.806 --> 00:20:08.042
I have good news. though.
The warrant to track
Antonio's phone came through.

376
00:20:08.176 --> 00:20:10.812
I found him. He's on the move.
but he's not far.

377
00:20:10.945 --> 00:20:11.979
[phone beeping]

378
00:20:12.379 --> 00:20:13.815
What's all that green?

379
00:20:14.381 --> 00:20:17.719
-[beeping continues]
-[birds chirping]

380
00:20:23.591 --> 00:20:25.927
So... [exhales]
...20 years with one person.

381
00:20:26.060 --> 00:20:29.496
then a four-month
ideal relationship
that you blew up on purpose.

382
00:20:29.630 --> 00:20:31.833
and now a situationship?

383
00:20:32.365 --> 00:20:35.603
You're missing
a little nuance. but yes.
those are the bullet points.

384
00:20:35.737 --> 00:20:37.304
How's the situationship going?

385
00:20:37.437 --> 00:20:40.273
It's great. You know.
we're kind of dating.

386
00:20:40.407 --> 00:20:41.776
There's nothing official.

387
00:20:41.909 --> 00:20:44.311
There are feelings.
but no commitment.

388
00:20:44.746 --> 00:20:47.215
And that's supposed to
make things less complicated?

389
00:20:47.582 --> 00:20:49.316
You know.
having no labels is wonderful.

390
00:20:49.449 --> 00:20:51.586
It's. uh. it's very liberating.

391
00:20:51.953 --> 00:20:53.487
Oh. Um...

392
00:20:54.555 --> 00:20:57.692
-That looks friendly.
-Don't worry.
it's not spider season.

393
00:20:58.826 --> 00:20:59.861
Right.

394
00:21:01.796 --> 00:21:05.265
Don't you wanna get married.
have kids and all that?

395
00:21:05.733 --> 00:21:08.268
[Will] Yes. I mean. you know.
when I meet the right person.

396
00:21:08.401 --> 00:21:10.470
How about you? You want kids?

397
00:21:12.673 --> 00:21:15.009
Very much so. Yeah.

398
00:21:16.043 --> 00:21:17.377
[phone beeping]

399
00:21:18.411 --> 00:21:19.747
Oh. no.

400
00:21:20.515 --> 00:21:22.884
-What's wrong?
-I lost the signal.

401
00:21:23.316 --> 00:21:24.719
Let me try over here.

402
00:21:28.288 --> 00:21:30.457
-[phone beeping]
-[Elkie sighs]

403
00:21:30.892 --> 00:21:32.492
Anything?

404
00:21:33.161 --> 00:21:35.495
-No. Shoot.
-[sighs]

405
00:21:35.630 --> 00:21:37.999
Let's just keep walking.
[screams]

406
00:21:38.132 --> 00:21:39.600
[grunts]

407
00:21:41.969 --> 00:21:44.304
[both groaning. panting]

408
00:21:45.206 --> 00:21:46.439
I got you.

409
00:21:47.575 --> 00:21:49.376
-Leave the pack.
-No. the phone's in it.

410
00:21:49.510 --> 00:21:52.647
-We'll have
no way of tracking him.
-Elkie. you're slipping.

411
00:21:55.315 --> 00:21:56.651
[groaning. panting]

412
00:21:56.784 --> 00:21:59.053
-Grab my arm with both hands.
-But I...

413
00:21:59.187 --> 00:22:01.022
Do it.

414
00:22:01.155 --> 00:22:02.389
Elkie.

415
00:22:03.057 --> 00:22:04.826
Do it. Elkie.

416
00:22:08.529 --> 00:22:09.564
[grunts] Okay.

417
00:22:09.697 --> 00:22:11.398
[Elkie straining. groaning]

418
00:22:25.279 --> 00:22:26.647
You okay?

419
00:22:27.380 --> 00:22:28.649
I'm okay.

420
00:22:31.219 --> 00:22:33.688
[grunts] The phone.

421
00:22:34.255 --> 00:22:35.723
I'm so sorry. Agent Trent.

422
00:22:35.857 --> 00:22:39.961
[sighs] Please. call me Will.

423
00:22:40.561 --> 00:22:41.796
Will.

424
00:22:51.739 --> 00:22:54.075
The good news is
I still have my phone.

425
00:22:54.809 --> 00:22:58.679
If we can get to an area
with reception. I can download
the tracking software.

426
00:22:59.412 --> 00:23:01.616
There's a signal tower
a few miles out.

427
00:23:02.049 --> 00:23:03.450
Well. let's get moving.

428
00:23:04.384 --> 00:23:05.485
-Thanks.
-Yeah.

429
00:23:05.620 --> 00:23:07.088
[baby crying in distance]

430
00:23:10.791 --> 00:23:12.526
Tell me you hear that too.

431
00:23:22.036 --> 00:23:23.838
[♪ suspenseful music plays]

432
00:23:34.815 --> 00:23:36.717
[Will] GBI. Anyone in there?

433
00:23:47.528 --> 00:23:48.930
What the hell?

434
00:24:03.077 --> 00:24:04.111
Mom.

435
00:24:12.219 --> 00:24:13.654
[baby crying]

436
00:24:17.224 --> 00:24:18.592
[♪ eerie music plays]

437
00:24:24.332 --> 00:24:27.535
[baby crying]

438
00:24:36.744 --> 00:24:38.245
[crying continues]

439
00:24:49.357 --> 00:24:50.725
[crying stops]

440
00:24:54.095 --> 00:24:55.563
Will.

441
00:24:57.732 --> 00:24:59.033
What is it?

442
00:25:00.334 --> 00:25:01.902
It's a tape recorder.

443
00:25:04.739 --> 00:25:06.040
And a dummy.

444
00:25:09.343 --> 00:25:10.678
Antonio's phone.

445
00:25:11.212 --> 00:25:12.246
He was here.

446
00:25:12.713 --> 00:25:14.215
Now we can't track him.

447
00:25:14.682 --> 00:25:15.883
[sighs]

448
00:25:21.322 --> 00:25:22.690
[♪ somber music plays]

449
00:25:41.075 --> 00:25:43.744
[screams]

450
00:25:44.345 --> 00:25:45.713
[panting]

451
00:25:47.281 --> 00:25:48.315
[James] Do it again.

452
00:25:49.383 --> 00:25:51.118
This time with feeling.

453
00:25:53.154 --> 00:25:53.988
[chuckles]

454
00:25:54.121 --> 00:25:56.057
[♪ suspenseful music plays]

455
00:25:57.091 --> 00:25:58.993
-[chuckles]
-What did you just do?

456
00:25:59.126 --> 00:26:00.995
Who else knows about
the necklace?

457
00:26:01.128 --> 00:26:02.430
No.

458
00:26:02.563 --> 00:26:04.932
This is a bridge too far.

459
00:26:05.066 --> 00:26:06.467
-I will not--
-The necklace!

460
00:26:06.600 --> 00:26:07.802
Please.

461
00:26:08.269 --> 00:26:09.603
I may be flawed.

462
00:26:10.371 --> 00:26:11.572
But leave me my dignity.

463
00:26:11.705 --> 00:26:13.007
Fine.

464
00:26:15.709 --> 00:26:17.011
Start talking.

465
00:26:17.144 --> 00:26:18.712
Well. Lucy wasn't wearing it
when she died.

466
00:26:18.846 --> 00:26:21.282
Amanda found it
after she was abducted.

467
00:26:21.415 --> 00:26:22.850
Then she gave it to you. right?

468
00:26:22.983 --> 00:26:25.853
Which makes our suspect list
real short. You. me...

469
00:26:25.986 --> 00:26:27.354
Oh. wait a minute.

470
00:26:27.488 --> 00:26:29.790
What's Amanda's alibi
the night in question?

471
00:26:30.324 --> 00:26:32.059
What about
your little fan club. huh?

472
00:26:32.193 --> 00:26:34.161
The freaks you wrote to
from prison?

473
00:26:34.295 --> 00:26:36.730
Oh. you don't think
I'd tell those losers
stuff about my life.

474
00:26:36.864 --> 00:26:38.866
Jeb Oswald.

475
00:26:38.999 --> 00:26:41.469
That man shows his willy
to little girls. I'd like to
think I have some standards.

476
00:26:41.602 --> 00:26:44.772
[exhales] You're right.
He's not your type at all.

477
00:26:44.905 --> 00:26:48.809
Exactly.
So. if I had nothing to do
with sending those letters...

478
00:26:49.944 --> 00:26:51.712
Then there's someone else
who knows

479
00:26:52.346 --> 00:26:54.315
about Antonio.
my mother. everything.

480
00:26:54.448 --> 00:26:56.317
[chuckles]
This feels good. doesn't it?

481
00:26:56.450 --> 00:26:58.886
Tête-à-tête. After this.
let's go into Old San Juan.

482
00:26:59.019 --> 00:27:00.454
I know a place
we can throw back some rum.

483
00:27:00.589 --> 00:27:02.656
get in some real trouble.
That's what partners do.

484
00:27:02.790 --> 00:27:05.059
So how does whoever is
sending these letters
know details about my life?

485
00:27:05.192 --> 00:27:09.029
[James] I never told anyone
about you. and I sure as hell
never mentioned Lucy.

486
00:27:09.163 --> 00:27:11.665
but you know me.

487
00:27:12.399 --> 00:27:17.171
There's nothing
I like more than savoring
the details of my own life.

488
00:27:19.807 --> 00:27:22.443
Eduardo. send a message
to Amanda Wagner.

489
00:27:22.577 --> 00:27:24.011
What if Ulster kept a journal?

490
00:27:24.145 --> 00:27:26.113
-Pfft.
-I know you tossed
his prison cell.

491
00:27:26.247 --> 00:27:28.749
but I think he's been
writing things down somewhere.

492
00:27:29.650 --> 00:27:31.085
Get a warrant if you have to.

493
00:27:32.486 --> 00:27:34.321
[Eduardo] <i>Message sent.</i>

494
00:27:38.859 --> 00:27:40.094
[Elkie] I found this.

495
00:27:40.529 --> 00:27:41.762
It was under the bed.

496
00:27:47.835 --> 00:27:49.236
I heard you scream.

497
00:27:51.739 --> 00:27:53.374
My mother died like this.

498
00:27:54.408 --> 00:27:55.442
In childbirth?

499
00:27:57.411 --> 00:27:58.746
Jesus. Will.

500
00:28:00.014 --> 00:28:01.348
It's a setup.

501
00:28:02.149 --> 00:28:05.152
Someone took Antonio
to mess with me.
to get me out here.

502
00:28:05.853 --> 00:28:08.289
-I should have never
come to San Juan.
-This isn't your fault.

503
00:28:08.422 --> 00:28:09.490
None of it.

504
00:28:09.624 --> 00:28:11.926
Not Antonio. Not Lucy.

505
00:28:14.161 --> 00:28:15.196
Will.

506
00:28:15.896 --> 00:28:17.298
Your hand.

507
00:28:18.432 --> 00:28:19.466
[Will exhales]

508
00:28:24.371 --> 00:28:25.406
There's something here.

509
00:28:26.307 --> 00:28:29.511
It's a message from Antonio.
Look.

510
00:28:30.010 --> 00:28:32.112
Why would he draw
a picture of a...

511
00:28:33.214 --> 00:28:35.149
<i>La Serpiente de Hierro.</i>

512
00:28:37.686 --> 00:28:39.053
The Iron Snake.

513
00:28:39.186 --> 00:28:41.422
It's an abandoned military base
way out in the jungle.

514
00:28:43.757 --> 00:28:45.893
-Will was right.
Ulster had a journal.
-[Amanda] Where is it?

515
00:28:46.026 --> 00:28:48.896
He gave it to his lawyer
to send to his next of kin
when he died.

516
00:28:49.029 --> 00:28:50.464
Next of kin. Who?

517
00:28:50.599 --> 00:28:51.832
[ringing]

518
00:28:57.539 --> 00:28:58.739
[person] Hello.

519
00:28:58.872 --> 00:29:00.274
[Faith] <i>Ms. Trevens?</i>

520
00:29:01.475 --> 00:29:03.444
[Ms. Trevens] Yes.

521
00:29:03.578 --> 00:29:05.647
This is Special Agent
Faith Mitchell with the Georgia
Bureau of Investigation.

522
00:29:05.779 --> 00:29:08.749
I'd like to speak to
your daughter. Adelaide.
Is she available?

523
00:29:08.882 --> 00:29:11.385
[Ms. Trevens sighs]
She's not here.

524
00:29:12.386 --> 00:29:13.521
What's she done?

525
00:29:13.921 --> 00:29:17.992
Did you work as
James Ulster's secretary
from 1986 to 1989?

526
00:29:18.125 --> 00:29:21.362
[Ms. Trevens] I-I don't
remember the exact dates.

527
00:29:21.495 --> 00:29:23.130
What's this about?

528
00:29:23.264 --> 00:29:24.932
[Faith] <i>Ms. Trevens. we spoke</i>
<i>to James Ulster's lawyer</i>

529
00:29:25.065 --> 00:29:26.333
<i>who confirmed that his effects.</i>

530
00:29:26.467 --> 00:29:28.402
including a journal
that he kept in prison.

531
00:29:28.536 --> 00:29:31.939
was sent to his next of kin...
[inhales]
...your daughter.

532
00:29:32.507 --> 00:29:33.708
Wha...

533
00:29:33.841 --> 00:29:36.243
Ms. Trevens.
Amanda Wagner. GBI.

534
00:29:36.745 --> 00:29:40.715
Adelaide is James Ulster's
daughter. correct?

535
00:29:40.848 --> 00:29:42.916
[Ms. Trevens exhales. stutters]

536
00:29:43.050 --> 00:29:45.587
James and I...
[stutters. sniffles]

537
00:29:46.086 --> 00:29:48.623
It was just a onetime thing.

538
00:29:49.591 --> 00:29:51.693
<i>He wanted</i>
<i>nothing to do with her.</i>

539
00:29:52.226 --> 00:29:56.930
She wrote him letters.
hundreds of letters.

540
00:29:57.798 --> 00:30:00.367
Never once
did he write her back.

541
00:30:00.501 --> 00:30:04.004
He would never have
sent her anything.

542
00:30:04.706 --> 00:30:08.242
Even so. we'd still
like to speak to her.
Do you know where she is?

543
00:30:09.544 --> 00:30:11.579
She's visiting
her new girlfriend.

544
00:30:11.713 --> 00:30:13.682
Some woman she met online.

545
00:30:13.814 --> 00:30:15.583
-[Faith] <i>Do you know</i>
<i>that woman's name?</i>
-[Ms. Trevens] I don't know.

546
00:30:15.717 --> 00:30:17.451
<i>I just know where she lives.</i>

547
00:30:17.585 --> 00:30:18.653
Where is that?

548
00:30:18.787 --> 00:30:21.523
San Juan. Puerto Rico.

549
00:30:21.656 --> 00:30:23.357
[♪ ominous music plays]

550
00:30:33.901 --> 00:30:35.135
This is it.

551
00:30:43.877 --> 00:30:46.947
If Antonio's in there.
they must have found
another way inside.

552
00:30:59.460 --> 00:31:01.563
[Will] Looks like
an old sewer access.

553
00:31:02.062 --> 00:31:03.397
After you?

554
00:31:04.064 --> 00:31:05.499
[♪ pensive music plays]

555
00:31:23.818 --> 00:31:24.918
[insect scuttling]

556
00:31:25.052 --> 00:31:26.588
What was that?

557
00:31:28.122 --> 00:31:29.356
[scuttling]

558
00:31:31.925 --> 00:31:32.861
[Will exhales]

559
00:31:32.993 --> 00:31:35.095
Not spider season. huh?

560
00:31:36.865 --> 00:31:38.399
Are they poisonous?

561
00:31:38.833 --> 00:31:40.067
Very.

562
00:31:40.668 --> 00:31:42.035
[Will sighs]

563
00:32:04.091 --> 00:32:05.492
[smacking flashlight]

564
00:32:05.627 --> 00:32:08.362
-Unbelievable. Battery died.
-[Elkie exhales]

565
00:32:08.495 --> 00:32:10.397
-You have extras?
-Other pack.

566
00:32:10.832 --> 00:32:11.999
[Will exhales]

567
00:32:12.132 --> 00:32:14.368
-Perfect.
-Here. give me the bag.

568
00:32:16.771 --> 00:32:18.540
[spiders scuttling]

569
00:32:18.673 --> 00:32:19.707
What's that?

570
00:32:27.181 --> 00:32:29.450
Go. Go. go. go. go. go.

571
00:32:40.595 --> 00:32:41.995
[panting]

572
00:32:47.936 --> 00:32:49.436
[Elkie shrieks]

573
00:32:51.138 --> 00:32:54.709
Thank God for these sleeves.
You didn't get bitten. did you?
[panting]

574
00:32:54.843 --> 00:32:56.578
I don't-I don't know. [panting]

575
00:32:59.848 --> 00:33:02.115
[Elkie] Okay. okay. Uh...

576
00:33:02.249 --> 00:33:03.518
Oh. One bite is okay.

577
00:33:03.651 --> 00:33:05.587
We just need to get you
to the hospital.

578
00:33:06.153 --> 00:33:07.622
We don't have time for that.

579
00:33:09.056 --> 00:33:10.290
Will. stop.

580
00:33:12.827 --> 00:33:14.161
-What the--
-[shrieks]

581
00:33:18.600 --> 00:33:19.868
Oh. my God.

582
00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:21.703
What? What is it?

583
00:33:21.836 --> 00:33:23.437
[Elkie panting]

584
00:33:29.309 --> 00:33:31.613
This is it. Adelaide's
rental apartment.

585
00:33:34.816 --> 00:33:36.751
Adelaide Trevens! GBI!

586
00:33:54.334 --> 00:33:56.436
-Bedroom's clear.
-[Michael] Hey. Faith.

587
00:33:57.137 --> 00:33:58.372
Check this out.

588
00:33:59.941 --> 00:34:01.141
It's Ulster's Journal.

589
00:34:01.275 --> 00:34:04.111
It has everything
about Will. Lucy.

590
00:34:04.679 --> 00:34:05.713
It's all here.

591
00:34:09.182 --> 00:34:11.519
-How bad is it?
-Bad. [breathes heavily]

592
00:34:12.119 --> 00:34:15.455
-Will it kill me?
-Yes. if you don't get
antivenom.

593
00:34:18.693 --> 00:34:19.627
How long?

594
00:34:19.761 --> 00:34:21.796
Ten hours. tops.

595
00:34:23.063 --> 00:34:24.197
Okay.

596
00:34:25.065 --> 00:34:28.368
Will. the more you move.
the faster the poison
will spread to your heart.

597
00:34:29.403 --> 00:34:31.104
[person groaning in distance]

598
00:34:31.238 --> 00:34:32.472
Antonio.

599
00:34:33.841 --> 00:34:35.409
Antonio!

600
00:34:35.877 --> 00:34:37.444
[groaning continues]

601
00:34:47.287 --> 00:34:48.422
Ormewood.

602
00:34:48.556 --> 00:34:49.724
Antonio.

603
00:34:52.159 --> 00:34:53.427
[groaning]

604
00:34:53.561 --> 00:34:54.762
Antonio.

605
00:35:02.336 --> 00:35:03.470
[chuckles]

606
00:35:03.605 --> 00:35:06.473
[cackles]

607
00:35:10.845 --> 00:35:13.213
-[Will grunts]
-[person cackling]

608
00:35:14.348 --> 00:35:15.817
[grunting]

609
00:35:18.953 --> 00:35:20.387
[♪ eerie music plays]

610
00:35:29.864 --> 00:35:31.131
Jesus.

611
00:35:33.467 --> 00:35:37.137
Whoo. whoo. [cackles. grunts]

612
00:35:37.270 --> 00:35:39.306
[breathes heavily]

613
00:35:48.415 --> 00:35:50.585
Lana Elkie. FBI.

614
00:35:57.625 --> 00:35:59.761
-[Elkie panting]
-[person wheezing]

615
00:36:00.628 --> 00:36:02.396
-[person thuds]
-[Will panting]

616
00:36:04.799 --> 00:36:06.534
I wasn't gonna
let him kill you.

617
00:36:11.839 --> 00:36:13.206
I wanna do that myself.

618
00:36:13.340 --> 00:36:14.776
[♪ ominous music plays]

619
00:36:19.647 --> 00:36:21.348
Slide me your weapon.

620
00:36:32.259 --> 00:36:33.661
Cute.

621
00:36:34.227 --> 00:36:39.667
All these hours together
and I still have no idea
what my father saw in you.

622
00:36:40.467 --> 00:36:42.235
He never mentioned you.

623
00:36:43.671 --> 00:36:45.773
If I was a boy.
maybe he would have.

624
00:36:48.876 --> 00:36:50.878
I'm so much more like him
than you'll ever be.

625
00:36:51.012 --> 00:36:53.380
-Won't get any arguments
from me there.
-Stay where you are.

626
00:36:53.514 --> 00:36:55.850
-Where's my uncle?
-Guess you'll never know.

627
00:36:55.983 --> 00:36:57.652
Where is he?

628
00:36:57.785 --> 00:37:01.756
My dad spent
his last precious time
on Earth behind bars.

629
00:37:02.890 --> 00:37:05.760
-Now. you'll do the same.
-Oh. is that
what this is about?

630
00:37:06.326 --> 00:37:08.395
Huh? Revenge?

631
00:37:13.233 --> 00:37:14.602
What's wrong?

632
00:37:14.736 --> 00:37:15.770
[clanking]

633
00:37:16.170 --> 00:37:17.772
You looking for these?

634
00:37:18.906 --> 00:37:20.708
[Elkie grunts]

635
00:37:20.842 --> 00:37:23.544
I knew when you said her name.

636
00:37:24.812 --> 00:37:25.847
Lucy.

637
00:37:26.781 --> 00:37:28.549
I never told you her name.

638
00:37:28.983 --> 00:37:30.417
[chuckles]

639
00:37:30.551 --> 00:37:33.721
And yet you let me bring you
all the way out here.

640
00:37:33.855 --> 00:37:35.355
What can I say?

641
00:37:36.524 --> 00:37:37.992
I liked your company.

642
00:37:41.195 --> 00:37:42.830
Is he one of your pen pals?

643
00:37:43.564 --> 00:37:44.498
How many are there?

644
00:37:44.632 --> 00:37:46.500
Too many to count.

645
00:37:46.634 --> 00:37:50.605
Oh. but do they know it was you
they were talking to.

646
00:37:51.105 --> 00:37:52.874
and not your daddy? [chuckles]

647
00:37:54.341 --> 00:37:56.844
They would be so disappointed.

648
00:38:01.414 --> 00:38:02.750
Goodbye. Will Trent.

649
00:38:05.285 --> 00:38:06.654
[Will scoffs]

650
00:38:06.788 --> 00:38:07.822
[clinking]

651
00:38:10.024 --> 00:38:11.159
[Will scoffs]

652
00:38:11.291 --> 00:38:12.960
[Adelaide groans]

653
00:38:13.493 --> 00:38:15.462
[yelps. panting]

654
00:38:19.100 --> 00:38:21.102
Let me out. you son of a bitch!

655
00:38:21.235 --> 00:38:22.804
Let me out!

656
00:38:24.172 --> 00:38:25.640
[groaning]

657
00:38:28.743 --> 00:38:30.678
I'm gonna kill you!

658
00:38:30.812 --> 00:38:34.314
-[Will breathes heavily]
-[Adelaide] No!

659
00:38:36.951 --> 00:38:38.385
Antonio!

660
00:38:39.287 --> 00:38:40.453
[breathes heavily]

661
00:38:40.588 --> 00:38:42.056
[Adelaide] Damn you!

662
00:38:44.525 --> 00:38:45.927
Damn you!

663
00:38:51.464 --> 00:38:52.834
[Adelaide] I'm gonna kill you!

664
00:38:55.670 --> 00:38:57.572
-[groans]
-[birds chirping]

665
00:39:02.677 --> 00:39:03.911
[Faith] Oh. Okay.

666
00:39:06.346 --> 00:39:08.381
Jesus.
Be careful with that thing.

667
00:39:08.516 --> 00:39:10.218
-Oh. sorry.
-Okay.

668
00:39:10.350 --> 00:39:11.886
I hope this is right.

669
00:39:12.485 --> 00:39:14.454
Well. she had the map
at her place.

670
00:39:14.589 --> 00:39:16.524
unless she's into
tropical topography.

671
00:39:16.657 --> 00:39:19.060
[Faith] Yeah. it should be
right around here.
but I don't see anything.

672
00:39:20.761 --> 00:39:22.563
Come on. Will. help us out.

673
00:39:23.331 --> 00:39:24.599
Will!

674
00:39:34.242 --> 00:39:37.078
[bird chirping]

675
00:39:37.211 --> 00:39:39.847
[wings fluttering]

676
00:39:39.981 --> 00:39:41.949
[waves lapping]

677
00:39:45.720 --> 00:39:48.022
[Lucy] Lay your head
on my lap. <i>Papito.</i>

678
00:39:48.488 --> 00:39:49.857
The ground is so hard.

679
00:39:51.424 --> 00:39:52.927
[Lucy] <i>Mmm.</i>

680
00:39:54.862 --> 00:39:56.764
Doesn't look good. does it?

681
00:39:56.898 --> 00:39:57.932
Shh.

682
00:39:59.133 --> 00:40:00.868
It'll all work out.

683
00:40:02.036 --> 00:40:04.705
Will we be together
on the other side?

684
00:40:04.839 --> 00:40:06.807
[Lucy]
We're already together. <i>Papi.</i>

685
00:40:09.243 --> 00:40:10.711
We always have been.

686
00:40:14.115 --> 00:40:16.117
I wanted more than this.

687
00:40:21.188 --> 00:40:22.890
I wanted a family.

688
00:40:26.127 --> 00:40:27.962
Then scream. Will.

689
00:40:29.363 --> 00:40:30.698
<i>Scream.</i>

690
00:40:32.633 --> 00:40:34.302
[no audible dialogue]

691
00:40:34.434 --> 00:40:35.970
[♪ sorrowful music plays]

692
00:40:38.406 --> 00:40:43.811
[Will screams. echoing]

693
00:40:49.083 --> 00:40:50.450
[Faith] Will?

694
00:40:50.952 --> 00:40:51.953
Will?

695
00:40:54.355 --> 00:40:55.589
Faith.

696
00:40:56.557 --> 00:40:57.490
Will. Will.

697
00:40:57.625 --> 00:40:59.026
-Call a medevac.
-Yeah.

698
00:40:59.160 --> 00:41:00.127
[beeps]

699
00:41:00.895 --> 00:41:03.898
Get me a priority medevac.
I'm sending the coordinates
right now.

700
00:41:04.532 --> 00:41:05.933
What happened?

701
00:41:06.067 --> 00:41:07.201
Spiders.

702
00:41:07.335 --> 00:41:08.736
Poison.

703
00:41:09.870 --> 00:41:11.572
She's in the cell.

704
00:41:11.706 --> 00:41:14.608
Ulster's daughter.
She knows where my uncle is.

705
00:41:15.209 --> 00:41:17.845
Go. go. It's okay.
It's gonna be okay.

706
00:41:17.979 --> 00:41:20.214
-Stay with me.
-[Michael] Adelaide?

707
00:41:40.001 --> 00:41:41.035
Adelaide?

708
00:41:53.714 --> 00:41:54.949
[exhales]

709
00:42:06.961 --> 00:42:09.263
Hey. hey.
Will. Will. stay with me.

710
00:42:09.397 --> 00:42:10.531
Help is on the way. okay?

711
00:42:10.664 --> 00:42:12.133
-What'd she say?
-She wasn't there.

712
00:42:12.266 --> 00:42:14.735
I searched
the whole place. Will.

713
00:42:15.469 --> 00:42:17.705
I'm sorry. bud. She's gone.

714
00:42:18.272 --> 00:42:21.876
[Faith] Stay with me.
Hey. hey. Will? Will?

715
00:42:22.009 --> 00:42:23.911
[distorted] Will. stay with me.

715
00:42:24.305 --> 00:43:24.167
